{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Fire|type2=Normal}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Fire|prevnum=666|prev=Vivillon|nextnum=668|next=Pyroar}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Litleo\n|jname=シシコ\n|tmname=Shishiko\n|category=Lion Cub\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Fire\n|type2=Normal\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Rivalry\n|ability2=Unnerve\n|abilityd=Moxie\n|ndex=667\n|karea=Central\n|kdex=057\n|height-ftin=2\'00"\n|height-m=0.6\n|weight-lbs=29.8\n|weight-kg=13.5\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Field\n|gendercode=223\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=1\n|evsa=1\n|expyield=74\n|lv100exp=1,059,860\n|color=Brown\n|catchrate=220\n|body=08\n|pokefordex=litleo\n|generation=6\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Litleo\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'シシコ\'\'\' \'\'Shishiko\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Fire|Normal}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation VI]].\n\nIt [[evolution|evolves]] into {{p|Pyroar}} starting at [[level]] 35.\n\n==Biology==\nLitleo is a quadruped, leonine Pokémon. It is mostly dark brown with pale brown paws, ears, tail tip, and face. It has a short, rounded muzzle with a reddish orange nose, round ears with darker interiors,  and circular, black eyes with white pupils. There is a reddish orange tuft of fur between its ears. Each of its paws has three toes and dark brown paw pads. The tail ends in a pointed, teardrop shape.\n\nLitleo is a hot-blooded Pokémon that is curious by nature and is quick to start fights. In battle, its short mane radiates heat. The stronger its opponent, the more heat it produces. When a wild Litleo is capable of hunting on its own, it is kicked out of the pride and begins to live alone. In the past, {{m|Noble Roar}} was its [[signature move]].\n\n==In the anime==\n===Major appearances===\n[[File:Litleo anime.png|thumb|left|250px|Litleo in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\nLitleo debuted in \'\'[[PK26|Pikachu, What\'s This Key?]]\'\'. It was a resident of a world full of ice and snow, which was accessed by {{AP|Pikachu}} and his friends, courtesy of {{p|Klefki}}\'s keys.\n\nFour Litleo appeared in \'\'[[XY097|A Fiery Rite of Passage!]]\'\'. One of them was forced to leave the pride by {{p|Pyroar}}, but with {{Ash}}\'s help, it was able to become independent and leave its pride.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nLitleo made its main series debut in \'\'[[XY080|Performing with Fiery Charm!]]\'\', under the ownership of a {{pkmn|Performer}} competing in the {{to|Dendemille}} {{pkmn|Showcase}}. It reappeared in \'\'[[XY091|A Performance Pop Quiz!]]\'\', where it participated in the {{ci|Anistar}} Showcase; and in \'\'[[XY109|Master Class Choices!]]\'\', where it participated in the {{ci|Fleurrh}} Showcase. It reappeared once more in \'\'[[XY112|Master Class is in Session!]]\'\', where it was used in the Master Class Showcase in [[Gloire City]].\n\nMultiple Litleo appeared in \'\'[[M19|Volcanion and the Mechanical Marvel]]\'\', including one during a flashback. Another was seen as a resident of the [[Nebel Plateau]].\n\nTwo Litleo appeared during a flashback in \'\'[[XYS05|The Legend of X, Y, and Z!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo {{pkmn|Trainer}}s\' Litleo appeared in \'\'[[SM034|A Crowning Moment of Truth!]]\'\'. They were among the Pokémon attending the [[Wela Fire Festival\u200e]].\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Kalos}}\n{{Animedexbody|XY097|Litleo|Ash\'s Pokédex|Litleo, the Lion Cub Pokémon. Litleo must leave its pride and fend for itself in order to grow up strong.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'XY\'\'|Kalos}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Manabu Litleo.png|thumb|left|140px|Litleo in [[Let\'s Play the Pokémon Card Game XY!]]]]\n===In the movie adaptations===\nA Litleo appeared in the {{ma|Volcanion and the Mechanical Marvel|manga adaptation}} of \'\'[[M19|Volcanion and the Mechanical Marvel]]\'\' as a resident of the [[Nebel Plateau]].\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nA Litleo owned by a girl in [[Vaniville Town]] is seen running away with her in \'\'[[PAXY02|X-actly What They Wanted]]\'\'.\n\nA Litleo appeared with a {{tc|Preschooler}} in [[Lumiose City]] in \'\'[[PAXY10|Pangoro Poses a Problem]]\'\'.\n\nA {{pkmn2|wild}} Litleo appeared in \'\'[[PAXY05|Kangaskhan...Kangascan\'t]]\'\', where it was battling {{adv|X}} while he was {{pkmn|training}} on {{rt|22|Kalos}}.\n\n===In the Let\'s Play the Pokémon Card Game XY! manga===\n[[Manabu Kadoo|Manabu]] used a Litleo that later can evolve into a male {{p|Pyroar}} in Let\'s Play the Pokémon Card Game XY!.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Litleo (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=fire|type2=normal}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|num1=057|label1=Central|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=The stronger the opponent it faces, the more heat surges from its mane and the more power flows through its body.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=They set off on their own from their pride and live by themselves to become stronger. These hot-blooded Pokémon are quick to fight.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Omega Ruby|t=FFF|entry=The stronger the opponent it faces, the more heat surges from its mane and the more power flows through its body.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Alpha Sapphire|t=FFF|entry=They set off on their own from their pride and live by themselves to become stronger. These hot-blooded Pokémon are quick to fight.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VII|reg1=Alola|num1=370|label1={{gameabbrev7|USUM}}:|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/NE|[[Pokémon Sun and Moon|Sun, Moon]], [[Pokémon: Let\'s Go, Pikachu! and Let\'s Go, Eevee!|Let\'s Go, Pikachu! and Let\'s Go, Eevee!]]\u200e}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Ultra Sun|entry=When they\'re young, they live with a pride. Once they\'re able to hunt prey on their own, they\'re kicked out and have to make their own way.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Ultra Moon|entry=This hot-blooded Pokémon is filled with curiosity. When it gets angry or starts fighting, its short mane gets hot.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Footer}}\n\n===Game locations===\n{{Availability/Header|type=fire